Crate root for ctx-verify — a broker that runs cargo/clippy/script checks and emits one capped JSON report, keeping verification-cost bounded and deterministic (same report-schema family as the spec-audit tool).

No logic lives here beyond module wiring: `cli` (argv/io) sits over `checks` (pure orchestration) sits over `runner` (the actual process-spawning boundary). `parse` turns each check's structured or `FAIL:`-line output into the shared `model` types; `error` holds the crate's error enum. Editors adding a new check type should extend `checks`+`parse`+`model` together, not bypass the layering by calling `runner` directly from `cli`.